nen Lucan die Bürgerkriegsthematik literarisiert. Das Epos steht zugleich inner- und außerhalb der Gattungstradition und konfrontiert seine Leserschaft mit einer neuartigen Ästhetik.  aLucan’s Bellum Civile is one of the most impressive and unusual works of Silver Age Latin literature, and has been the subject of much research in recent years. In this volume well-known experts on Lucan examine the poetological, narratological and stylistic techniques the author employed to write on the theme of civil war. The epic poem is at once both conforms to and exceeds the tradition of the genre, and confronts its readers with a new kind of aesthetic.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCivil war in literature. 0aEpic poetry, LatinxHistory and criticism. 4aBellum Civile. 4aBürgerkrieg. 4aEpos. 4aLucan. 4aPharsalia. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Rome.2bisacsh  aBellum Civile.  aCivil War.  aEpos.  aLucan.  aPharsalia.1 aAhl, Frederick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAmbühl, Annemarie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBexley, Erica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDinter, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFantham, Elaine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHömke, Nicola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHömke, Nicola, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLowe, Dunstan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoura, Alessandro Rolim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReitz, Christiane, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSannicandro, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https